        public static Vec3 findEndpoint(Vec3 startPoint,
                                Vec3 directions)
        Finds the endpoint of a line given the startpoint, the radius, the angle from the x axis, and the angle on the z axis
        NOTE: This method interprets the second vector as (Distance, Angle on X, Angle on Z)
        NOTE: The angles given are presumed to be in radians
        Parameters:
        startPoint - Starting point of the line segment
        directions - Direction vector (Distance, Angle on X, Angle on Z)
        Returns:
        The endpoint of the line
